        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "The pyright issue has nothing to do with dynamic registration, it is just a casualty of dynamic registration support, since it causes the server to switch to pull mode.\n https://github.com/DetachHead/basedpyright/blob/f0ab53bb61c42a29ef2d4a1fc418cdba52157604/packages/pyright-internal/src/languageServerBase.ts#L709-L711\n\nThere appears to be a bug there, where `workspace/diagnostics` doesn't work correctly unless the client supports streaming of the diagnostics via LSP partial results mechanism. If i hack a token into the neovim request, then I see the diagnostics flow, otherwise no response:\n\n```diff\n--- a/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/diagnostic.lua\n+++ b/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/diagnostic.lua\n@@ -563,6 +563,7 @@ function M._workspace_diagnostics(opts)\n       local params = {\n         identifier = cap.identifier,\n         previousResultIds = previous_result_ids(client.id, cap.identifier),\n+        partialResultToken = 42\n       }\n \n       client:request('workspace/diagnostic', params, handler)\n```\n\n```text\n[DEBUG][2026-04-14 22:02:24] /usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/log.lua:151\t\"rpc.receive\"\t{ jsonrpc = \"2.0\", method = \"$/progress\", params = { token = 42, value = { items = { { diagnostics = { { code = \"reportArgumentType\", codeDescription = { href = \"https://docs.basedpyright.com/v1.39.0/configuration/config-files/#reportArgumentType\" }, message = 'Argument of type \"Literal[42]\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"sep\" of type \"str | None\" .........\n```\n\nSo that's how the feature is working for vscode but not for neovim. I believe the bug is here, I will do some more archaeology and try to file problem on the pyright side:\nhttps://github.com/DetachHead/basedpyright/blob/f0ab53bb61c42a29ef2d4a1fc418cdba52157604/packages/pyright-internal/src/languageServerBase.ts#L357-L363\n\nImplementing streaming on the neovim side seems non-trivial, for now I recommend this workaround in your LSP configuration:\n```lua\n  -- workspace pulls don't work correctly without partial result token\n  init_options = {\n    disablePullDiagnostics = true\n  },\n```",
